title: Extend provider config for OpenAI Codex OAuth credentials
---
## Requirements

- Extend `Runtime_config.provider_config` and config loading/serialization so a provider can use ChatGPT subscription auth instead of a static `api_key`.
- Support persisted OAuth credentials for OpenAI Codex (`access_token`, `refresh_token`, `expires`, optional `account_id`, optional `email`) while keeping existing API-key providers backward compatible.
- Update secret encryption/redaction paths so Codex OAuth secrets are stored securely and `config show` remains safe.
- Update provider selection helpers so a provider with valid Codex OAuth credentials counts as configured even when `api_key` is empty.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Config round-trips with a provider auth mode for OpenAI Codex without breaking existing provider entries.
- Secret-store encryption covers the new OAuth credential fields.
- Provider selection no longer requires a literal API key when Codex OAuth creds are present.
- Relevant OCaml tests pass.
